natural vocalizations; song? from one bird displaying to another.  This pair had two very young chicks, and these could be alarm calls, but the behavior suggest otherwise.  While giving these calls, the bird calling stood up taller and straighter than usual, and walked a tight circle around the second bird (which can be heard giving some quiet calls in the background of this cut).  I heard this exchange three times, and the other two were longer (6-7 notes), but this is the only one I could get on tape.  These birds were in boggy ground along a small stream above timberline.bird-seen:yes playback-used:no
